prompt:
Add a public async function called BackgroundProcessAsync to AsyncOps.calr that uses ConfigureAwait(false) for better performance in library code. It returns Task<i32>.

Use this exact Calor ConfigureAwait syntax:
§AF{f001:BackgroundProcessAsync:pub}
  §O{Task<i32>}
  §E{net:r}
  §B{result} §AWAIT{false} §C{SlowOperationAsync}§/C
  §R result
§/AF{f001}

The §AWAIT{false} syntax specifies ConfigureAwait:
- §AWAIT{false} = ConfigureAwait(false), doesn't capture context
- §AWAIT{true} or §AWAIT = ConfigureAwait(true), captures context
- Use false in library code for better performance
